<dl id="n03055a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03055a">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03055a"> 55(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ever &amp; always <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n03055a"> <li>FW prototext </li><li><ms href="#n03055a">MS BL 47482b-7</ms> </li><li>JJA 57:015 <a name="qA0d" href="../../ff/fdra/qda.htm#qA0d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/q/qa0d.htm#n03055a">Draft: III&sect;2A.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">But too late, too late. Three dreadful blows were struck on that partition towards which we were all looking, and an aged but vigorous and indignant voice cried out above the storm in ringing Irish: &ldquo;Am I to be kept always in the dark? <mark>Ever and always!</mark> Look at me, and I for the last hour killed with listening to your foolery and dogs and giggling and the stranger&apos;s voice stunning me; and &apos;tisn&apos;t worth your while, Shawn, to come in with a little word.&rdquo; <small> Daniel Corkery, <a name="DCHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DCHB"><cite title="source">The Hounds of Banba</cite></a> (1920) 44</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
